HEADWORD: Scrog
<hw>Scrog</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Scrag</er>, or
Gael. <ets>sgrogag</ets> anything shriveled, from <ets>sgrog</ets> to
compress, shrivel.]</ety> <def>A stunted shrub, bush, or branch.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

